    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-08-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-08-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="523"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d523">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Frederick W. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to"
                        >Mr. Pruyn</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 73.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-08-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 29, 1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your despatch of the 26th of May last, (No. 38,)
                    with its several accompaniments, has been received. The information it contains
                    had already been received by the department, through Lord Lyons, from the
                    British government, and the views of this government upon the very important
                    subject to which your correspondence with Sir Rutherford Alcock relates, were
                    communicated to you in the instruction from this department of the 20th instant,
                    (No. 71.) It is, therefore, not necessary that I should do more at present than
                    acknowledge the receipt of your No. 38.</p>
                <p>I am sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FREDERICK W. SEWARD, <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert H. Pruyn</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                            &amp;c., &amp;c., Kanagawa.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
